{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775859352694,"sessionID":"ses_2868919c7ffebiv27BUPS9ii6Y","part":{"id":"prt_d797744740011kIOk5PV9AK5M1","messageID":"msg_d7977409a001Y4v1df1Gpnez92","sessionID":"ses_2868919c7ffebiv27BUPS9ii6Y","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859509302,"sessionID":"ses_2868919c7ffebiv27BUPS9ii6Y","part":{"id":"prt_d7979a7bd001id4mUGBbt4FXDY","messageID":"msg_d7977409a001Y4v1df1Gpnez92","sessionID":"ses_2868919c7ffebiv27BUPS9ii6Y","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-fc40eda0b03d431e9976e2e2cb366307","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n\n## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n**Module**: `pkg/picod`\n**Language**: Go\n**Purpose**: Extend PicoD file management capabilities with Kubernetes client-go integration, enabling centralized management of PicoD instances and their workspaces through custom Kubernetes resources (AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter).\n\n## Overview\n\nPicoD file management API provides secure file operations within isolated workspace jails. AR-016 enhances this by integrating with Kubernetes through the generated client-go library, allowing PicoD instances to be managed as Kubernetes resources while maintaining existing HTTP-based file management APIs. This integration enables lifecycle management, health monitoring, and workspace orchestration at the Kubernetes level.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- Maintain existing HTTP-based file management APIs (upload, list, download)\n- Integrate with Kubernetes client-go for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n- Support workspace provisioning and management through Kubernetes custom resources\n- Enable health status reporting to Kubernetes via status subresource\n- Provide watch/informer capabilities for real-time resource updates\n- Maintain workspace jail security and path sanitization\n- Support graceful shutdown and cleanup of workspaces\n- Enable multi-tenant isolation through namespace separation\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── auth.go                    # JWT authentication (existing)\n├── execute.go                 # Command execution (existing)\n├── files.go                   # File management handlers (existing)\n├── server.go                  # HTTP server (existing)\n├── handlers.go                # HTTP handlers (existing)\n├── middleware.go              # Middleware (existing)\n├── errors.go                  # Error handling (existing)\n├── config.go                  # Configuration (existing)\n├── constants.go               # Constants (existing)\n├── k8s_integration.go         # NEW: Kubernetes client integration\n├── workspace_manager.go       # NEW: Workspace lifecycle management\n├── status_reporter.go         # NEW: Status reporting to Kubernetes\n└── informer.go                # NEW: Resource informers and event handlers\n\nchanges/AR-016/\n├── design.md                  # This document\n├── spec.md                    # API specification\n├── CHANGE.md                  # Change log\n└── IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md  # Implementation summary\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Kubernetes Cluster                               │\n│                                                                          │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                   API Server                                     │   │\n│  │  - AgentRuntime CRD                                              │   │\n│  │  - CodeInterpreter CRD                                           │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                │                                        │\n│                                │ REST API                               │\n│                                │                                        │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                 PicoD Controller (Optional)                       │  │\n│  │  - Creates/updates AgentRuntime resources                         │  │\n│  │  - Manages PicoD instance lifecycle                               │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                                                                          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                  │\n                                  │ HTTP API (JWT Auth)\n                                  │\n┌─────────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          PicoD Instance                                  │\n│                                                                           │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │              HTTP Server (Gin)                                  │     │\n│  │  - /api/execute                                                │     │\n│  │  - /api/files (upload, list, download)                          │     │\n│  │  - /health                                                      │     │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n│                                  │                                        │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │         Kubernetes Client Integration                           │     │\n│  │  - Clientset for Runtime API                                    │     │\n│  │  - Informers for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter                   │     │\n│  │  - Status reporting (UpdateStatus)                              │     │\n│  │  - Watch events (Add, Update, Delete)                           │     │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n│                                  │                                        │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │         Workspace Manager                                       │     │\n│  │  - Workspace provisioning                                       │     │\n│  │  - Path sanitization and jail enforcement                       │     │\n│  │  - File operations (upload, list, download)                     │     │\n│  │  - Cleanup and garbage collection                               │     │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n│                                  │                                        │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │         Status Reporter                                         │     │\n│  │  - Health status aggregation                                     │     │\n│  │  - File system statistics                                       │     │\n│  │  - Resource usage metrics                                       │     │\n│  │  - Error conditions and events                                  │     │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n│                                                                           │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                  │\n                                  │\n┌─────────────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Shared Workspace Volume                                │\n│                                                                           │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │         Workspace Directory                                     │     │\n│  │  - User files                                                   │     │\n│  │  - Code artifacts                                               │     │\n│  │  - Execution outputs                                            │     │\n│  │  - Temporary files                                              │     │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n│                                                                           │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow with Kubernetes Integration\n\n```\n1. Kubernetes Resource Creation\n   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   │ User/Controller creates AgentRuntime CRD instance           │\n   │                                                              │\n   │ apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1           │\n   │ kind: AgentRuntime                                           │\n   │ metadata:                                                    │\n   │   name: my-agent                                             │\n   │   namespace: default                                         │\n   │ spec:                                                        │\n   │   image: volcano-sh/agentcube-agent:latest                   │\n   │   workspaceSize: \"1Gi\"                                       │\n   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                           │\n                           ▼\n   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   │ Kubernetes API Server validates and stores the resource     │\n   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                           │\n                           ▼\n   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   │ PicoD Pod scheduled with AgentRuntime reference             │\n   │ Environment variables injected:                             │\n   │ - AGENTRUNTIME_NAME, AGENTRUNTIME_NAMESPACE                 │\n   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n2. PicoD Initialization\n   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   │ PicoD starts and initializes Kubernetes client              │\n   │                                                              │\n   │ - Loads in-cluster configuration                            │\n   │ - Creates clientset for Runtime API                         │\n   │ - Starts informers for AgentRuntime resources               │\n   │ - Retrieves corresponding AgentRuntime resource            │\n   │ - Provisions workspace directory                            │\n   │ - Starts status reporter goroutine                          │\n   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n3. File Management Operations (HTTP API)\n   POST /api/files\n   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   │ HTTP Request (JWT authenticated)                             │\n   │ - Upload file to workspace                                   │\n   │                                                              │\n   │ PicoD processes:                                             │\n   │ - Validates JWT token                                        │\n   │ - Sanitizes file path                                        │\n   │ - Writes file to workspace                                   │\n   │ - Updates workspace statistics                              │\n   │ - Triggers status update (async)                             │\n   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n4. Status Reporting (Async)\n   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   │ Status Reporter periodically updates Kubernetes             │\n   │                                                              │\n   │ - Collects file system stats                                 │\n   │ - Aggregates health status                                   │\n   │ - Calls client.UpdateStatus()                                │\n   │                                                              │\n   │ Status subresource updated:                                  │\n   │ status:                                                      │\n   │   phase: \"Running\"                                           │\n   │   workspace:                                                 │\n   │     fileCount: 42                                            │\n   │     totalSize: \"1024MiB\"                                     │\n   │     lastModified: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"                     │\n   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n5. Watch Events (Informers)\n   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   │ Informer receives events from Kubernetes                    │\n   │                                                              │\n   │ - AgentRuntime deleted → Cleanup workspace, shutdown        │\n   │ - AgentRuntime updated → Apply configuration changes        │\n   │ - ConfigMap changed → Reload configuration                  │\n   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Kubernetes Client Integration\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/k8s_integration.go`\n\n```go\n// K8sClient manages Kubernetes client operations\ntype K8sClient struct {\n\tclientset       *agentcubeclientset.Clientset\n\tagentRuntimeClient runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInterface\n\tcodeInterpreterClient runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInterface\n\tnamespace       string\n\tagentRuntimeName string\n\tinformerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n\tstopCh          chan struct{}\n}\n\n// K8sConfig holds Kubernetes client configuration\ntype K8sConfig struct {\n\tInCluster      bool\n\tKubeconfigPath string\n\tNamespace      string\n\tAgentRuntimeName string\n\tAgentRuntimeNamespace string\n}\n\n// NewK8sClient creates a new Kubernetes client\nfunc NewK8sClient(config K8sConfig) (*K8sClient, error) {\n\tvar kubeConfig *rest.Config\n\tvar err error\n\n\tif config.InCluster {\n\t\tkubeConfig, err = rest.InClusterConfig()\n\t} else if config.KubeconfigPath != \"\" {\n\t\tkubeConfig, err = clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", config.KubeconfigPath)\n\t} else {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"either in-cluster or kubeconfig path must be specified\")\n\t}\n\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build kubeconfig: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tclientset, err := agentcubeclientset.NewForConfig(kubeConfig)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create clientset: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tnamespace := config.Namespace\n\tif namespace == \"\" {\n\t\tif config.InCluster {\n\t\t\tnamespaceBytes, err := os.ReadFile(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/namespace\")\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to read namespace from service account: %w\", err)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tnamespace = string(namespaceBytes)\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tnamespace = \"default\"\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tinformerFactory := informers.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, time.Minute*10)\n\n\treturn &K8sClient{\n\t\tclientset:            clientset,\n\t\tagentRuntimeClient:   clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace),\n\t\tcodeInterpreterClient: clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace),\n\t\tnamespace:            namespace,\n\t\tagentRuntimeName:     config.AgentRuntimeName,\n\t\tstopCh:               make(chan struct{}),\n\t\tinformerFactory:      informerFactory,\n\t}, nil\n}\n\n// GetAgentRuntime retrieves the AgentRuntime resource\nfunc (k *K8sClient) GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n\treturn k.agentRuntimeClient.Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n}\n\n// UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus updates the status subresource\nfunc (k *K8sClient) UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n\treturn k.agentRuntimeClient.UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n}\n\n// GetCodeInterpreter retrieves the CodeInterpreter resource\nfunc (k *K8sClient) GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n\treturn k.codeInterpreterClient.Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n}\n\n// UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus updates the status subresource\nfunc (k *K8sClient) UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus(ctx context.Context, codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n\treturn k.codeInterpreterClient.UpdateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n}\n\n// StartInformers starts the informers and waits for cache sync\nfunc (k *K8sClient) StartInformers() {\n\tk.informerFactory.Start(k.stopCh)\n}\n\n// WaitForCacheSync waits for informer caches to sync\nfunc (k *K8sClient) WaitForCacheSync() map[reflect.Type]bool {\n\treturn k.informerFactory.WaitForCacheSync(k.stopCh)\n}\n\n// Stop stops the informers\nfunc (k *K8sClient) Stop() {\n\tclose(k.stopCh)\n}\n```\n\n### Workspace Manager\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/workspace_manager.go`\n\n```go\n// WorkspaceManager manages workspace lifecycle\ntype WorkspaceManager struct {\n\tworkspaceDir     string\n\tk8sClient       *K8sClient\n\tmetrics         WorkspaceMetrics\n\tmetricsMutex    sync.RWMutex\n}\n\n// WorkspaceMetrics holds workspace statistics\ntype WorkspaceMetrics struct {\n\tFileCount       int64     `json:\"file_count\"`\n\tTotalSize       int64     `json:\"total_size\"`\n\tLastModified    time.Time `json:\"last_modified\"`\n\tDirectoryCount  int64     `json:\"directory_count\"`\n}\n\n// NewWorkspaceManager creates a new workspace manager\nfunc NewWorkspaceManager(workspaceDir string, k8sClient *K8sClient) (*WorkspaceManager, error) {\n\tif err := os.MkdirAll(workspaceDir, DefaultDirMode); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create workspace directory: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn &WorkspaceManager{\n\t\tworkspaceDir: workspaceDir,\n\t\tk8sClient:   k8sClient,\n\t\tmetrics:     WorkspaceMetrics{},\n\t}, nil\n}\n\n// ProvisionWorkspace provisions a new workspace directory\nfunc (wm *WorkspaceManager) ProvisionWorkspace() error {\n\tif err := os.MkdirAll(wm.workspaceDir, DefaultDirMode); err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to provision workspace: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// CleanupWorkspace cleans up the workspace directory\nfunc (wm *WorkspaceManager) CleanupWorkspace() error {\n\tif err := os.RemoveAll(wm.workspaceDir); err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to cleanup workspace: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// UpdateMetrics updates workspace metrics\nfunc (wm *WorkspaceManager) UpdateMetrics() error {\n\tmetrics, err := wm.calculateMetrics()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to calculate workspace metrics: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\twm.metricsMutex.Lock()\n\twm.metrics = metrics\n\twm.metricsMutex.Unlock()\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// calculateMetrics calculates workspace statistics\nfunc (wm *WorkspaceManager) calculateMetrics() (WorkspaceMetrics, error) {\n\tvar metrics WorkspaceMetrics\n\tvar totalSize int64\n\tvar fileCount, dirCount int64\n\tvar lastModified time.Time\n\n\terr := filepath.Walk(wm.workspaceDir, func(path string, info os.FileInfo, err error) error {\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tif info.IsDir() {\n\t\t\tdirCount++\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tfileCount++\n\t\t\ttotalSize += info.Size()\n\t\t\tif info.ModTime().After(lastModified) {\n\t\t\t\tlastModified = info.ModTime()\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\treturn nil\n\t})\n\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn WorkspaceMetrics{}, err\n\t}\n\n\tmetrics.FileCount = fileCount\n\tmetrics.TotalSize = totalSize\n\tmetrics.LastModified = lastModified\n\tmetrics.DirectoryCount = dirCount\n\n\treturn metrics, nil\n}\n\n// GetMetrics returns current workspace metrics\nfunc (wm *WorkspaceManager) GetMetrics() WorkspaceMetrics {\n\twm.metricsMutex.RLock()\n\tdefer wm.metricsMutex.RUnlock()\n\treturn wm.metrics\n}\n```\n\n### Status Reporter\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/status_reporter.go`\n\n```go\n// StatusReporter reports status to Kubernetes\ntype StatusReporter struct {\n\tk8sClient       *K8sClient\n\tworkspaceManager *WorkspaceManager\n\tagentRuntimeName string\n\tinterval        time.Duration\n\tstopCh          chan struct{}\n}\n\n// NewStatusReporter creates a new status reporter\nfunc NewStatusReporter(k8sClient *K8sClient, workspaceManager *WorkspaceManager, agentRuntimeName string, interval time.Duration) *StatusReporter {\n\treturn &StatusReporter{\n\t\tk8sClient:        k8sClient,\n\t\tworkspaceManager: workspaceManager,\n\t\tagentRuntimeName: agentRuntimeName,\n\t\tinterval:        interval,\n\t\tstopCh:          make(chan struct{}),\n\t}\n}\n\n// Start starts the status reporter\nfunc (sr *StatusReporter) Start() {\n\tticker := time.NewTicker(sr.interval)\n\tdefer ticker.Stop()\n\n\tfor {\n\t\tselect {\n\t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n\t\t\tif err := sr.reportStatus(); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to report status: %v\", err)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\tcase <-sr.stopCh:\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\n// Stop stops the status reporter\nfunc (sr *StatusReporter) Stop() {\n\tclose(sr.stopCh)\n}\n\n// reportStatus reports the current status to Kubernetes\nfunc (sr *StatusReporter) reportStatus() error {\n\tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 10*time.Second)\n\tdefer cancel()\n\n\tagentRuntime, err := sr.k8sClient.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, sr.agentRuntimeName)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get AgentRuntime: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tif err := sr.workspaceManager.UpdateMetrics(); err != nil {\n\t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to update workspace metrics: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tmetrics := sr.workspaceManager.GetMetrics()\n\n\tagentRuntime.Status.Phase = \"Running\"\n\tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.FileCount = metrics.FileCount\n\tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.TotalSize = metrics.TotalSize\n\tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.LastModified = metav1.NewTime(metrics.LastModified)\n\tagentRuntime.Status.Workspace.DirectoryCount = metrics.DirectoryCount\n\n\t_, err = sr.k8sClient.UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, agentRuntime)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update AgentRuntime status: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tklog.V(2).Infof(\"Successfully reported status for AgentRuntime %s\", sr.agentRuntimeName)\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n### Informer Event Handlers\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/informer.go`\n\n```go\n// InformerManager manages informer event handlers\ntype InformerManager struct {\n\tk8sClient         *K8sClient\n\tserver            *Server\n\tworkspaceManager  *WorkspaceManager\n}\n\n// NewInformerManager creates a new informer manager\nfunc NewInformerManager(k8sClient *K8sClient, server *Server, workspaceManager *WorkspaceManager) *InformerManager {\n\treturn &InformerManager{\n\t\tk8sClient:        k8sClient,\n\t\tserver:           server,\n\t\tworkspaceManager: workspaceManager,\n\t}\n}\n\n// SetupAgentRuntimeInformer sets up AgentRuntime informer\nfunc (im *InformerManager) SetupAgentRuntimeInformer() {\n\tinformer := im.k8sClient.informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()\n\n\tinformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n\t\tAddFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n\t\t\tagentRuntime := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime %s added\", agentRuntime.Name)\n\t\t},\n\t\tUpdateFunc: func(oldObj, newObj interface{}) {\n\t\t\toldAgentRuntime := oldObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n\t\t\tnewAgentRuntime := newObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n\n\t\t\tif !reflect.DeepEqual(oldAgentRuntime.Spec, newAgentRuntime.Spec) {\n\t\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime %s spec updated\", newAgentRuntime.Name)\n\t\t\t\tim.handleSpecUpdate(newAgentRuntime)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t\tDeleteFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n\t\t\tagentRuntime := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime)\n\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"AgentRuntime %s deleted, initiating shutdown\", agentRuntime.Name)\n\t\t\tim.handleAgentRuntimeDeletion(agentRuntime)\n\t\t},\n\t})\n}\n\n// SetupCodeInterpreterInformer sets up CodeInterpreter informer\nfunc (im *InformerManager) SetupCodeInterpreterInformer() {\n\tinformer := im.k8sClient.informerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()\n\n\tinformer.AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n\t\tAddFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n\t\t\tcodeInterpreter := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s added\", codeInterpreter.Name)\n\t\t},\n\t\tUpdateFunc: func(oldObj, newObj interface{}) {\n\t\t\toldCodeInterpreter := oldObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n\t\t\tnewCodeInterpreter := newObj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n\n\t\t\tif !reflect.DeepEqual(oldCodeInterpreter.Spec, newCodeInterpreter.Spec) {\n\t\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s spec updated\", newCodeInterpreter.Name)\n\t\t\t\tim.handleCodeInterpreterUpdate(newCodeInterpreter)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t\tDeleteFunc: func(obj interface{}) {\n\t\t\tcodeInterpreter := obj.(*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter)\n\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s deleted\", codeInterpreter.Name)\n\t\t},\n\t})\n}\n\n// handleSpecUpdate handles AgentRuntime spec updates\nfunc (im *InformerManager) handleSpecUpdate(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) {\n\tif agentRuntime.Spec.WorkspaceSize != nil {\n\t\tklog.Infof(\"Workspace size updated to %s\", *agentRuntime.Spec.WorkspaceSize)\n\t}\n\n\tif agentRuntime.Spec.TerminationGracePeriodSeconds != nil {\n\t\tklog.Infof(\"Termination grace period updated to %d\", *agentRuntime.Spec.TerminationGracePeriodSeconds)\n\t}\n}\n\n// handleAgentRuntimeDeletion handles AgentRuntime deletion\nfunc (im *InformerManager) handleAgentRuntimeDeletion(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) {\n\tif agentRuntime.Name == im.k8sClient.agentRuntimeName {\n\t\tklog.Info(\"This PicoD instance's AgentRuntime was deleted, initiating graceful shutdown\")\n\n\t\tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n\t\tdefer cancel()\n\n\t\tif err := im.workspaceManager.CleanupWorkspace(); err != nil {\n\t\t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to cleanup workspace: %v\", err)\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tif err := im.server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n\t\t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to shutdown server: %v\", err)\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tos.Exit(0)\n\t}\n}\n\n// handleCodeInterpreterUpdate handles CodeInterpreter updates\nfunc (im *InformerManager) handleCodeInterpreterUpdate(codeInterpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) {\n\tif codeInterpreter.Spec.RuntimeName == im.k8sClient.agentRuntimeName {\n\t\tklog.Infof(\"CodeInterpreter %s for this runtime updated\", codeInterpreter.Name)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Server Integration\n\n**Modified File**: `pkg/picod/server.go`\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n\tengine           *gin.Engine\n\tconfig           Config\n\tauthManager      *AuthManager\n\tstartTime        time.Time\n\tworkspaceDir     string\n\thttpServer       *http.Server\n\tk8sClient        *K8sClient\n\tworkspaceManager *WorkspaceManager\n\tstatusReporter   *StatusReporter\n\tinformerManager  *InformerManager\n}\n\nfunc NewServer(config Config) (*Server, error) {\n\tworkspace := config.Workspace\n\tif workspace == \"\" {\n\t\tcwd, err := os.Getwd()\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to get current working directory\", err.Error(), err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tworkspace = cwd\n\t}\n\n\tabsWorkspace, err := filepath.Abs(workspace)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to resolve workspace path\", err.Error(), err)\n\t}\n\n\tif err := os.MkdirAll(absWorkspace, DefaultDirMode); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, NewError(ErrServerInternal, \"failed to create workspace directory\", err.Error(), err)\n\t}\n\n\tauthManager, err := NewAuthManager()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\tgin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)\n\tengine := gin.New()\n\tengine.Use(gin.Recovery())\n\tengine.Use(gin.Logger())\n\n\tserver := &Server{\n\t\tengine:       engine,\n\t\tconfig:       config,\n\t\tauthManager:  authManager,\n\t\tstartTime:    time.Now(),\n\t\tworkspaceDir: absWorkspace,\n\t}\n\n\tserver.registerRoutes()\n\n\tif config.K8sConfig != nil {\n\t\tk8sClient, err := NewK8sClient(*config.K8sConfig)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to create Kubernetes client: %v\", err)\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tserver.k8sClient = k8sClient\n\n\t\t\tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(absWorkspace, k8sClient)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to create workspace manager: %v\", err)\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tserver.workspaceManager = workspaceManager\n\n\t\t\t\tif k8sClient.agentRuntimeName != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\t\tstatusReporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, k8sClient.agentRuntimeName, time.Minute)\n\t\t\t\t\tserver.statusReporter = statusReporter\n\t\t\t\t\tgo statusReporter.Start()\n\n\t\t\t\t\tinformerManager := NewInformerManager(k8sClient, server, workspaceManager)\n\t\t\t\t\tserver.informerManager = informerManager\n\t\t\t\t\tinformerManager.SetupAgentRuntimeInformer()\n\t\t\t\t\tinformerManager.SetupCodeInterpreterInformer()\n\n\t\t\t\t\tk8sClient.StartInformers()\n\t\t\t\t\tsynced := k8sClient.WaitForCacheSync()\n\t\t\t\t\tklog.Infof(\"Informer cache sync: %v\", synced)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn server, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *Server) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n\tklog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n\n\tif s.statusReporter != nil {\n\t\ts.statusReporter.Stop()\n\t}\n\n\tif s.k8sClient != nil {\n\t\ts.k8sClient.Stop()\n\t}\n\n\tif err := s.httpServer.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\n\tklog.Info(\"Server shutdown complete\")\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n### Configuration Extension\n\n**Modified File**: `pkg/picod/config.go`\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n\tPort      int          `json:\"port\"`\n\tWorkspace string       `json:\"workspace\"`\n\tK8sConfig *K8sConfig   `json:\"k8s_config,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype K8sConfig struct {\n\tInCluster           bool   `json:\"in_cluster\"`\n\tKubeconfigPath      string `json:\"kubeconfig_path\"`\n\tNamespace           string `json:\"namespace\"`\n\tAgentRuntimeName    string `json:\"agent_runtime_name\"`\n\tAgentRuntimeNamespace string `json:\"agent_runtime_namespace\"`\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Existing HTTP APIs (Unchanged)\n\nAll existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged:\n\n- **POST /api/execute**: Execute commands in workspace\n- **POST /api/files**: Upload files to workspace (multipart or JSON Base64)\n- **GET /api/files**: List files in workspace directory\n- **GET /api/files/*path**: Download files from workspace\n- **GET /health**: Health check (no authentication)\n\n### Kubernetes Resource Status\n\nThe AgentRuntime status subresource is updated with workspace information:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: my-agent\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  image: volcano-sh/agentcube-agent:latest\n  workspaceSize: \"1Gi\"\nstatus:\n  phase: \"Running\"\n  workspace:\n    fileCount: 42\n    totalSize: 1073741824\n    lastModified: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n    directoryCount: 8\n  conditions:\n    - type: \"Ready\"\n      status: \"True\"\n      lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n      reason: \"WorkspaceInitialized\"\n      message: \"Workspace initialized and ready\"\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Kubernetes Integration Errors\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/errors.go` (Extended)\n\n```go\nconst (\n\t// Kubernetes errors\n\tErrK8sConnectionFailed    = \"K8sConnectionFailed\"\n\tErrK8sResourceNotFound    = \"K8sResourceNotFound\"\n\tErrK8sUpdateFailed        = \"K8sUpdateFailed\"\n\tErrK8sInformerFailed      = \"K8sInformerFailed\"\n\tErrK8sConfigInvalid       = \"K8sConfigInvalid\"\n\n\t// Workspace errors\n\tErrWorkspaceProvisionFailed = \"WorkspaceProvisionFailed\"\n\tErrWorkspaceCleanupFailed   = \"WorkspaceCleanupFailed\"\n\tErrWorkspaceMetricsFailed   = \"WorkspaceMetricsFailed\"\n)\n\nvar statusCodeMap = map[string]int{\n\t// Existing error codes...\n\tErrK8sConnectionFailed:      http.StatusServiceUnavailable,\n\tErrK8sResourceNotFound:      http.StatusNotFound,\n\tErrK8sUpdateFailed:          http.StatusInternalServerError,\n\tErrK8sInformerFailed:        http.StatusInternalServerError,\n\tErrK8sConfigInvalid:         http.StatusBadRequest,\n\tErrWorkspaceProvisionFailed: http.StatusInternalServerError,\n\tErrWorkspaceCleanupFailed:   http.StatusInternalServerError,\n\tErrWorkspaceMetricsFailed:   http.StatusInternalServerError,\n}\n```\n\n### Error Recovery Strategy\n\n1. **Kubernetes Connection Failures**:\n   - Log error and continue in degraded mode (HTTP APIs still work)\n   - Retry connection with exponential backoff\n   - Mark Kubernetes integration as unavailable in health check\n\n2. **Resource Update Failures**:\n   - Retry with backoff (up to 5 attempts)\n   - Log error and continue (non-critical)\n   - Queue status update for next reporting cycle\n\n3. **Informer Failures**:\n   - Restart informer with backoff\n   - Log error and continue\n   - Health check indicates informer status\n\n4. **Workspace Failures**:\n   - Log error and fail the operation\n   - Return HTTP 500 to client\n   - Update Kubernetes status with error condition\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/k8s_integration_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestK8sClientCreation(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname        string\n\t\tconfig      K8sConfig\n\t\tsetupEnv    func()\n\t\tcleanupEnv  func()\n\t\twantErr     bool\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"in-cluster config\",\n\t\t\tconfig: K8sConfig{\n\t\t\t\tInCluster: true,\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: false,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"kubeconfig path\",\n\t\t\tconfig: K8sConfig{\n\t\t\t\tKubeconfigPath: \"/tmp/test-kubeconfig\",\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: false,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:   \"no config\",\n\t\t\tconfig: K8sConfig{},\n\t\t\twantErr: true,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tif tt.setupEnv != nil {\n\t\t\t\ttt.setupEnv()\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif tt.cleanupEnv != nil {\n\t\t\t\tdefer tt.cleanupEnv()\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tclient, err := NewK8sClient(tt.config)\n\t\t\tif (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"NewK8sClient() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tif !tt.wantErr && client != nil {\n\t\t\t\tif client.namespace == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected non-empty namespace\")\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestK8sClientOperations(t *testing.T) {\n\tif testing.Short() {\n\t\tt.Skip(\"Skipping integration test in short mode\")\n\t}\n\n\tclient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n\tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, client)\n\n\tctx := context.Background()\n\n\tt.Run(\"get non-existent resource\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t_, err := client.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, \"non-existent\")\n\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected error for non-existent resource\")\n\t\t}\n\t})\n\n\tt.Run(\"update status\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n\t\t\t\tName: \"test-agent\",\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tStatus: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n\t\t\t\tPhase: \"Running\",\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t}\n\n\t\t_, err := client.UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, agentRuntime)\n\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\tt.Error(\"Expected error for non-existent resource\")\n\t\t}\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/workspace_manager_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestWorkspaceManager(t *testing.T) {\n\tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n\tk8sClient := &K8sClient{}\n\n\tmanager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tt.Run(\"provision workspace\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\terr := manager.ProvisionWorkspace()\n\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\t\tif _, err := os.Stat(workspace); os.IsNotExist(err) {\n\t\t\tt.Error(\"Workspace directory should exist\")\n\t\t}\n\t})\n\n\tt.Run(\"update metrics on empty workspace\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\terr := manager.UpdateMetrics()\n\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\t\tmetrics := manager.GetMetrics()\n\t\tif metrics.FileCount != 0 {\n\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected 0 files, got %d\", metrics.FileCount)\n\t\t}\n\t})\n\n\tt.Run(\"update metrics with files\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\ttestFile := filepath.Join(workspace, \"test.txt\")\n\t\terr := os.WriteFile(testFile, []byte(\"test content\"), 0644)\n\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\t\terr = manager.UpdateMetrics()\n\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\t\tmetrics := manager.GetMetrics()\n\t\tif metrics.FileCount != 1 {\n\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected 1 file, got %d\", metrics.FileCount)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif metrics.TotalSize != len(\"test content\") {\n\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"Expected size %d, got %d\", len(\"test content\"), metrics.TotalSize)\n\t\t}\n\t})\n\n\tt.Run(\"cleanup workspace\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\terr := manager.CleanupWorkspace()\n\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\t\tif _, err := os.Stat(workspace); !os.IsNotExist(err) {\n\t\t\tt.Error(\"Workspace directory should not exist after cleanup\")\n\t\t}\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/status_reporter_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestStatusReporter(t *testing.T) {\n\tk8sClient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n\tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, k8sClient)\n\n\tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n\tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\treporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, \"test-agent\", time.Second)\n\n\tt.Run(\"report status\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\terr := reporter.reportStatus()\n\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\t})\n}\n\nfunc TestStatusReporterStart(t *testing.T) {\n\tk8sClient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n\tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, k8sClient)\n\n\tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n\tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\treporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, \"test-agent\", 100*time.Millisecond)\n\n\tgo reporter.Start()\n\n\ttime.Sleep(300 * time.Millisecond)\n\n\treporter.Stop()\n}\n```\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/informer_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestInformerManager(t *testing.T) {\n\tk8sClient := setupTestK8sClient(t)\n\tdefer cleanupTestK8sClient(t, k8sClient)\n\n\tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n\tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tserver := &Server{}\n\tinformerManager := NewInformerManager(k8sClient, server, workspaceManager)\n\n\tt.Run(\"setup agent runtime informer\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\tinformerManager.SetupAgentRuntimeInformer()\n\t})\n\n\tt.Run(\"setup code interpreter informer\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\tinformerManager.SetupCodeInterpreterInformer()\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `pkg/picod/k8s_integration_test.go`\n\n```go\nfunc TestK8sIntegrationFullWorkflow(t *testing.T) {\n\tif testing.Short() {\n\t\tt.Skip(\"Skipping integration test in short mode\")\n\t}\n\n\tctx := context.Background()\n\n\tworkspace := t.TempDir()\n\n\tk8sConfig := K8sConfig{\n\t\tInCluster:           false,\n\t\tKubeconfigPath:      os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\"),\n\t\tNamespace:           \"default\",\n\t\tAgentRuntimeName:    \"test-agent-runtime\",\n\t}\n\n\tk8sClient, err := NewK8sClient(k8sConfig)\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\tdefer k8sClient.Stop()\n\n\tworkspaceManager, err := NewWorkspaceManager(workspace, k8sClient)\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\tstatusReporter := NewStatusReporter(k8sClient, workspaceManager, \"test-agent-runtime\", time.Second)\n\tgo statusReporter.Start()\n\tdefer statusReporter.Stop()\n\n\tinformerManager := NewInformerManager(k8sClient, &Server{}, workspaceManager)\n\tinformerManager.SetupAgentRuntimeInformer()\n\n\tk8sClient.StartInformers()\n\tsynced := k8sClient.WaitForCacheSync()\n\trequire.True(t, synced.All())\n\n\tt.Run(\"workspace provisioning and metrics\", func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\ttestFile := filepath.Join(workspace, \"test.txt\")\n\t\terr := os.WriteFile(testFile, []byte(\"test content\"), 0644)\n\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\t\terr = workspaceManager.UpdateMetrics()\n\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\t\tmetrics := workspaceManager.GetMetrics()\n\t\trequire.Equal(t, int64(1), metrics.FileCount)\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Go Module Dependencies (Extended)\n\n```go\nrequire (\n    github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0\n    github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.0\n    k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1\n    github.com/stretchr/testify v1.9.0\n    k8s.io/client-go v0.30.3\n    k8s.io/apimachinery v0.30.3\n    k8s.io/api v0.30.3\n    github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go v0.0.1\n)\n```\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n- **Gin Framework**: HTTP routing and middleware (existing)\n- **JWT Library**: RSA-based JWT token validation (existing)\n- **klog**: Structured logging (existing)\n- **Kubernetes client-go**: Kubernetes API client (new)\n- **AgentCube client-go**: Custom resource client (new)\n- **Go Standard Library**: exec, os, filepath, time, context, crypto/rsa (existing)\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Authentication and Authorization\n\n- All HTTP APIs continue to require JWT authentication (unchanged)\n- Kubernetes client uses in-cluster config or provided kubeconfig\n- RBAC permissions required for PicoD service account:\n  ```yaml\n  apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n  kind: Role\n  metadata:\n    name: picod-role\n  rules:\n  - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n    resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n    verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"updatestatus\"]\n  ```\n\n### Workspace Security\n\n- Path sanitization unchanged (existing security measures maintained)\n- Workspace jail enforcement prevents directory traversal\n- Symlink resolution and validation (existing)\n- All file operations restricted to workspace directory\n\n### Kubernetes Integration Security\n\n- PicoD only updates status subresource, cannot modify spec\n- Limited RBAC permissions to prevent unauthorized modifications\n- Service account tokens used for authentication\n- No privileged access to cluster resources\n\n### Error Message Security\n\n- Error messages do not expose sensitive Kubernetes information\n- File paths in error messages remain relative to workspace\n- Kubernetes errors logged but not exposed to HTTP clients\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### With AgentCube Platform\n\nPicoD integrates with AgentCube components through Kubernetes resources:\n\n- **Sandbox Orchestrator**: Creates AgentRuntime resources referencing PicoD instances\n- **WorkloadManager**: Monitors AgentRuntime status for health and readiness\n- **Session Store**: Queries AgentRuntime resources for workspace information\n- **Controller**: Manages AgentRuntime lifecycle and configuration\n\n### Deployment Integration\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-pod\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  serviceAccountName: picod\n  containers:\n  - name: picod\n    image: volcano-sh/picod:latest\n    env:\n    - name: PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER\n      value: \"true\"\n    - name: PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME\n      valueFrom:\n        fieldRef:\n          fieldPath: metadata.annotations['agentcube.volcano.sh/agent-runtime']\n    - name: PICOD_K8S_NAMESPACE\n      valueFrom:\n        fieldRef:\n          fieldPath: metadata.namespace\n    - name: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n      valueFrom:\n        secretKeyRef:\n          name: picod-auth-keys\n          key: public-key\n    volumeMounts:\n    - name: workspace\n      mountPath: /workspace\n  volumes:\n  - name: workspace\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 1Gi\n```\n\n### Service Account\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: picod\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-role\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"updatestatus\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-role-binding\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: picod\nroleRef:\n  kind: Role\n  name: picod-role\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### CLI Flags (Extended)\n\n| Flag                | Type   | Default | Description |\n|---------------------|--------|---------|-------------|\n| `-port`             | int    | 8080    | Port for the PicoD server to listen on |\n| `-workspace`        | string | \"\"      | Root directory for file operations |\n| `-k8s-in-cluster`   | bool   | false   | Use in-cluster Kubernetes config |\n| `-k8s-kubeconfig`   | string | \"\"      | Path to kubeconfig file |\n| `-k8s-namespace`    | string | \"\"      | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `-k8s-agent-runtime`| string | \"\"      | AgentRuntime resource name |\n\n### Environment Variables (Extended)\n\n| Name                          | Required | Description |\n|-------------------------------|----------|-------------|\n| `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`       | Yes      | PEM-encoded RSA public key for JWT validation |\n| `PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER`        | No       | Set to \"true\" to use in-cluster config |\n| `PICOD_K8S_KUBECONFIG`        | No       | Path to kubeconfig file |\n| `PICOD_K8S_NAMESPACE`         | No       | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME`| No       | AgentRuntime resource name |\n\n### Configuration Example\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: picod-config\ndata:\n  PORT: \"8080\"\n  WORKSPACE: \"/workspace\"\n  PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY: |\n    -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n    MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEA...\n    -----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n  PICOD_K8S_IN_CLUSTER: \"true\"\n  PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME: \"my-agent-runtime\"\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\n### API Documentation\n\nAll existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged and documented in AR-015.\n\n### Kubernetes Integration Documentation\n\n**Setup PicoD with Kubernetes Integration**:\n```bash\n# Start PicoD with in-cluster config\n./picod -port 8080 -workspace /workspace -k8s-in-cluster -k8s-agent-runtime my-agent\n\n# Start PicoD with kubeconfig\n./picod -port 8080 -workspace /workspace -k8s-kubeconfig ~/.kube/config -k8s-agent-runtime my-agent -k8s-namespace default\n```\n\n**Monitoring AgentRuntime Status**:\n```bash\n# Get AgentRuntime status\nkubectl get agentruntime my-agent -o yaml\n\n# Watch AgentRuntime status updates\nkubectl get agentruntime my-agent -w\n\n# Get workspace statistics from status\nkubectl get agentruntime my-agent -o jsonpath='{.status.workspace}'\n```\n\n### Usage Examples\n\n**Deploy PicoD with Kubernetes Integration**:\n```yaml\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: picod\nspec:\n  replicas: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: picod\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: picod\n      annotations:\n        agentcube.volcano.sh/agent-runtime: my-agent\n    spec:\n      serviceAccountName: picod\n      containers:\n      - name: picod\n        image: volcano-sh/picod:latest\n        args:\n        - -port=8080\n        - -workspace=/workspace\n        - -k8s-in-cluster\n        env:\n        - name: PICOD_K8S_AGENT_RUNTIME_NAME\n          valueFrom:\n            fieldRef:\n              fieldPath: metadata.annotations['agentcube.volcano.sh/agent-runtime']\n        - name: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: picod-auth-keys\n              key: public-key\n        volumeMounts:\n        - name: workspace\n          mountPath: /workspace\n      volumes:\n      - name: workspace\n        emptyDir:\n          sizeLimit: 1Gi\n```\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] HTTP file management APIs continue to work unchanged\n- [ ] Kubernetes client successfully connects and authenticates\n- [ ] AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources can be retrieved\n- [ ] Status subresource updates succeed with workspace metrics\n- [ ] Informers receive and handle resource events correctly\n- [ ] Workspace manager provisions and cleans up workspaces\n- [ ] Status reporter periodically updates Kubernetes resources\n- [ ] Path sanitization and security remain effective\n- [ ] Error handling covers Kubernetes integration failures\n- [ ] Unit tests cover all new code paths\n- [ ] Integration tests validate Kubernetes workflows\n- [ ] RBAC permissions are correctly configured\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown handles Kubernetes resource deletion\n- [ ] Health check reflects Kubernetes integration status\n- [ ] Documentation covers setup and usage patterns\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- All existing HTTP APIs remain unchanged\n- Kubernetes integration is optional (disabled by default)\n- PicoD can run without Kubernetes client (degraded mode)\n- No breaking changes to existing deployments\n\n### Upgrading from AR-015\n\nTo enable Kubernetes integration:\n\n1. Update PicoD deployment to include service account\n2. Add RBAC role and role binding\n3. Configure environment variables for Kubernetes client\n4. Add `-k8s-in-cluster` flag or provide kubeconfig\n5. Specify AgentRuntime resource name via `-k8s-agent-runtime`\n6. Deploy updated ConfigMap with new configuration\n\n### Rollback Strategy\n\nIf Kubernetes integration causes issues:\n\n1. Remove `-k8s-in-cluster` and `-k8s-agent-runtime` flags\n2. PicoD will continue operating without Kubernetes integration\n3. HTTP APIs remain fully functional\n4. No data loss or workspace disruption\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n### Potential Future Features\n\n- Support for ConfigMap-based configuration updates\n- Integration with CodeInterpreter resources for execution tracking\n- Workspace backup and restore via Kubernetes resources\n- Multi-workspace support per AgentRuntime\n- Enhanced metrics via Prometheus endpoints\n- Event-based status updates (instead of periodic polling)\n- Support for workspace snapshots and versioning\n- Integration with Kubernetes volume provisioning\n- Custom resource definitions for workspace templates","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/op